    <!-- ===================== FAQ (dark) ===================== -->
    <section class="section faq" aria-labelledby="faq-title">
      <div class="container faq__grid">
        <aside class="faq__aside">
          <span class="eyebrow">(Common questions)</span>
          <h2 id="faq-title" class="faq__title">Frequently asked.</h2>
          <p class="faq__intro">The questions we hear most often from clients thinking about a private
            supply. If yours isn't answered here, get in touch, we'll answer plainly.</p>
        </aside>

        <div class="faq__list">
          <details class="faq__item">
            <summary class="faq__q">
              Do I need permission to install a borehole?
              <svg class="faq__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="faq__a">In most cases, no formal planning permission is required, though water
              abstraction over 20 cubic metres per day requires a licence from the Environment Agency.
              We handle the paperwork and liaison as part of any install where it's needed.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq__item">
            <summary class="faq__q">
              How long does a borehole and treatment system last?
              <svg class="faq__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="faq__a">A properly designed and installed system will run for 25–40 years with
              routine maintenance. Filtration media and UV lamps are consumables replaced on a service
              schedule. The borehole itself, the pump housing, and the treatment vessels are all
              long-life.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq__item">
            <summary class="faq__q">
              How often does the water need testing?
              <svg class="faq__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="faq__a">Annually as standard, though we recommend more frequent testing if your
              source water is known to be variable. All testing goes through a UKAS-accredited
              laboratory.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq__item">
            <summary class="faq__q">
              What happens if something goes wrong outside working hours?
              <svg class="faq__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="faq__a">Existing service clients have direct access to our engineers on a 24-hour
              emergency line. In most cases we can get to site within four hours of the call.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq__item">
            <summary class="faq__q">
              Can you take over servicing a system installed by someone else?
              <svg class="faq__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="faq__a">Yes, provided the system is safe to work on and we can access the plant.
              We start with a full inspection and water analysis, then propose any remedial work needed
              before taking on the ongoing service contract.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq__item">
            <summary class="faq__q">
              What does a typical install cost?
              <svg class="faq__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="faq__a">Every install is bespoke, so there is no typical figure. Costs depend on
              source depth, water chemistry, storage requirements and property demand. We provide a
              fixed-price quote after a site survey.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    
